[b]Chandelier Flip Radar [WavesUnchained][/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
ATR-based trailing stop that ratchets with price and flips between long and short mode when the close crosses the opposing stop level. The active stop holds while the trend holds and only re-seeds when an accepted flip occurs — a weak (body-rejected) close past the trigger never loosens it. On top of the binary flip, a directional state system makes trend weakening visible before the actual direction change: bars fade, turn yellow (warning zone), and turn orange (danger zone) as price approaches the flip trigger — while the stop line stays green/red so the trend direction is never lost.

[b]Key improvements over standard implementations[/b]
[list]
[*]The inactive stop is shown as a gray line — you see at a glance how far price must move to flip direction
[*]Warning/danger distance is measured to the real flip trigger (previous stop value), not the current stop
[*]A body filter gates the actual direction change: doji and inside-bar flips are ignored, not just unlabeled
[/list]

[b]Features[/b]
[list]
[*]Ratchet mechanism: active stop holds until an accepted flip, never loosened by a body-rejected break
[*]Extremum mode: close-based (default, smoother) or wick-based (more responsive)
[*]Directional state: strong / soft / danger per side — direction kept even in the danger zone
[*]Three flip qualities: confirmed flip, weak flip (body too weak), and trap (wick crossed but close held)
[*]Four adaptive multiplier modes: Off (fixed), Simple (volatility-regime scaling), K-means (self-selects the best-performing Chandelier factor), Conviction (trend-aware tightening/widening)
[*]K-means cluster selector (Best / Average / Worst) and performance-weighted AMA stop line
[*]Optional MTF confluence: higher-timeframe direction, pullback zones, diamond confluence flips
[*]Optional bar coloring by state, background fill, buy/sell labels at direction changes
[/list]

[b]Calculation[/b]
[list]
[*]Long stop = highest(close, period) − ATR × multiplier, ratcheted up only
[*]Short stop = lowest(close, period) + ATR × multiplier, ratcheted down only
[*]Direction flips to long when close > previous short stop; to short when close < previous long stop — only when the candle body passes the body filter
[/list]

[b]Alerts[/b]
Five named alert conditions: direction change, buy, sell, bull trap, bear trap. Also fires through a single "any alert() call" setup — on confirmed bars by default.

